<h1>From Edmund Pendleton</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Dear Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Decr 4 1773</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>I received yr Favr<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> &amp; am very glad you have made the purchase of Mr Black. I am Possessed of none of the title Deeds, probably Colo. Brooke may to whom I immediately wrote &amp; desired him, if he had, to forward them to Colo. Bassetts For you, or to Wmsburg to Mr Wythe, but have since heard he was not come home two days agoe.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0002" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> I imagine part of the conveyances are in the Secretarys Office, &amp; the residue in King &amp; Queen, I mean For the Estate in that County, the title to which I believe is all to be deduced From Joshua Story the Patentee.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0003" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> As to the King Wm Estate, I know we never had any papers, but a Mortgage from Colo. Moore &amp; a Release of the Equity of Redemption and Dower from him &amp; Mrs Moore.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0004" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0004-ptr">4</a> My wife<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0005" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0005-ptr">5</a> desires to be joined in Complts to Mrs Washington &amp; will be glad to see you in your way up, as well as Dr Sr Yr mo. hble Servt</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Edmd Pendleton</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Virginia Historical Society, Richmond ]">ViHi</span>: Lee Family Papers.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Letter not found.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>George Brooke (d. 1782) lived at Mantapike in King and Queen County on the Mattaponi and also owned land across the river in King William (8 <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ William Waller Hening, ed. &lt;i&gt;The Statutes at Large; Being a Collection of All the Laws of Virginia, from the First Session of the Legislature, in the Year 1619&lt;/i&gt;. 13 vols. 181923. Reprint. Charlottesville, Va., 1969. ]">Hening</span> 47475). Since 1767 Brooke had been employed by the trustees of John Robinsons estate, Edmund Pendleton and Peter Lyons, to aid in collecting debts owed to the estate (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ David John Mays, ed. &lt;i&gt;The Letters and Papers of Edmund Pendleton, 17341803&lt;/i&gt;. 2 vols. Charlottesville, Va., 1967. ]">Mays, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Pendleton Papers</span></span>, 1:36). Brooke wrote Bartholomew Dandridge on 8 Dec.: Colo. Washington desired I woud get what papers I had relative to the title of the Land he purchased of Mr Black in this County, and send them to you which I have now done. I believe there are other Deeds for small purchases made by Mr Robinson but they are not among the Papers in my Possession (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Virginia Historical Society, Richmond ]">ViHi</span>: George Bolling Lee Papers).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0320-0001&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0320-0001-fn-0001#GEWN-02-09-02-0320-0001-fn-0001" class="document">note 1 in the enclosure, Bartholomew Dandridge to GW, 30 December</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>For a description of Bernard Moores Romancoke plantation, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0286&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0286-fn-0003#GEWN-02-09-02-0286-fn-0003" class="document">GW to
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-09-02-pb-0400">[400]</span>
Robert Cary &amp; Co., 10 Nov., nn.3</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0286&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0286-fn-0006#GEWN-02-09-02-0286-fn-0006" class="document">6</a>. See also <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0320-0001&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0320-0001-fn-0004#GEWN-02-09-02-0320-0001-fn-0004" class="document">notes 4</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0320-0001&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0320-0001-fn-0007#GEWN-02-09-02-0320-0001-fn-0007" class="document">7 in the enclosure, Bartholomew Dandridge to GW, 30 December</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0298-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>Pendleton was married to Sarah Pollard Pendleton.</p>

</div>
</div>
